Naledi Shange, News24 (Picture: SA Para Limpopo via Twitter) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Polokwane &ndash; &nbsp;Three people have died in an accident on the N1 outside Polokwane on Thursday night, paramedics said.While the exact details about the crash were not immediately clear, the SA Para Limpopo group tweeted that six vehicles had been involved in the accident, which took place about 25km outside of Polokwane. The group posted a picture of the mangled remains of one of the vehicles, believed to be a Toyota Tazz. The vehicle's front and rear end were completely severed and its tyres had also come off.The highway was closed following the crash.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.